        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 3:51PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 351 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Buckhorn, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Buckhorn, Aldo Leopold Vista, and Portions of the Gila Wilderness.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
